# PyPocket Implementation Plan

PyPocket is a full-stack, mobile-first Python learning platform designed to feel like a combination of Duolingo, Notion, and Replit. It targets students who primarily or only own smartphones, meaning all UI/UX details, including the code editor and compiler output, must be optimized for small screens (320px to 768px), touch gestures, and low connectivity (PWA & client-side Pyodide compiler execution).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Google OAuth Auth**: We will implement a mockable JWT/OAuth integration. If you have production client IDs, they can be configured via environment variables.
> - **Sandbox Execution Security**: The backend Docker sandbox requires running a lightweight docker-in-docker or python-isolate sub-process container. We will implement a resource-limited execution runner using subprocess limits (Unix-compatible CPU/Memory/Network constraints) inside a containerized sandbox.
> - **Offline Sync**: For PWA client-side offline mode, we will cache the learning roadmap and compiler states via IndexedDB/localStorage. Streak and XP updates will sync once the client is online.

